Name: FOREST
Definition: Percentage of area covered by forest

Name: PRECIP
Definition: Basin average mean annual precipitation for 1981 to 2010 from PRISM

Name: DRNAREA
Definition: Area that contributes flow to a point on a stream (total drainage area minus non-contributing areas within basin)

Name: CANOPY_PCT
Definition: Percentage of drainage area covered by canopy comprised of classes 41-43 from 2001 National Land Cover Dataset

Name: JANMAXT2K
Definition: Mean Maximum January Temperature from 2K resolution PRISM 1961-1990 data

Name: I24H2Y
Definition: Maximum 24-hour precipitation that occurs on average once in 2 years - Equivalent to precitation intensity index

Name: LC11Forest
Definition: Percentage of forest from NLCD 2011 classes 41-43

Name: ELEV1K
Definition: Mean basin elevation in thousands of feet

Name: FORESTP1
Definition: Percentage of area covered by forest + 1%

Name: A7500
Definition: Percentage of the drainage area above 7,500ft elevation

Name: JANMINT2K
Definition: Mean Minimum January Temperature from 2K resolution PRISM 1961-1990 data

Name: MINANTEMP
Definition: Mean annual minimum air temperature in degrees Fahrenheit (PRISM)

Name: DRAINDENS
Definition: Basin drainage density; defined as total stream length divided by drainage area, in kilometers per square kilomete

Name: I6H100Y
Definition: Maximum 6-hour precipitation that occurs on average once in 100 years
